<p>The <b>UCLA Library Cataloging &amp; Metadata Center</b> provides 
e-resources metadata services for MARC and non-MARC description. </p>
<h2>MARC-based Services</h2>
<p>This Web section focuses on services related to MARC records for 
e-resources. Such services include </p>
<ul>
	<li>Coordinating&nbsp;new e-resources cataloging requests; </li>
	<li>Coordinating e-resource maintenance requests for bibliographic records 
	already in the library catalog;</li>
	<li>Developing &amp; refining load specifications for batch-loaded files of MARC records 
	(e.g.,&nbsp; SCP records and Marcive records);</li>
	<li>Developing and testing new tools to assist catalogers in providing 
	descriptive metadata for e-resources;</li>
	<li>Maintaining training &amp; documentation.</li>
</ul>
